  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best blogs about raising venture capital?",
  "response": "There are several high-quality blogs and resources focused on raising venture capital, discussing best practices, trends, and tips for startups. Here are some of the most recommended ones:\n\n1. **Both Sides of the Table** - Written by Mark Suster, a venture capitalist at Upfront Ventures, this blog provides insights from both the investor's and entrepreneur's perspectives.\n\n2. **Venture Hacks** - Founded by Naval Ravikant and Babak Nivi, this blog offers valuable advice on fundraising strategies, deal structures, and the overall venture capital landscape.\n\n3. **The Venture Capitalist** - This blog provides insights into the world of venture capital, including funding processes, startup advice, and market analysis.\n\n4. **A VC** - Fred Wilson\u2019s blog discusses technology, venture capital, and the intricacies of startups and fundraising.\n\n5. **Signal v. Noise** - From Basecamp, this blog covers a wide range of topics, including business, entrepreneurship, and insights into investment strategies.\n\n6. **Crunchbase News** - While more news-focused, Crunchbase provides valuable insights and trends in startups and venture capital funding rounds.\n\n7. **The Pitch** - A blog and podcast that focuses on the pitches made by entrepreneurs to investors, offering a deep dive into what works and what doesn\u2019t in fundraising.\n\n8. **SaaStr** - While primarily focused on SaaS companies, SaaStr offers tons of information on fundraising, scaling, and venture capital that\u2019s applicable to a wider range of startups.\n\n9. **First Round Review** - This blog by First Round Capital shares insights, lessons, and advice from successful entrepreneurs and investors on various topics, including fundraising.\n\n10. **The Funded** - This platform allows entrepreneurs to share their experiences with venture capitalists, providing insights into what to expect when raising capital.\n\nThese blogs cover a mix of practical advice, personal experiences, and industry trends related to raising venture capital, making them useful resources for entrepreneurs at various stages of their fundraising journey.",
